records.addlTxt:
Defendant Baakia Maurisa Clark in court with attorney Joseph Thomas Domask.   appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court made disclosure on the record.  The parties have no objection to this court proceeding on this matter.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction; STRAIGHT TIME.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions:  
*  No contact with any Kohl's Stores;
*  No contact with Brooklyn H.;
*  Complete HSED;
*  Maintain employment;
*  Perform 30 hours of community service;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Submit DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
